Q: In triangle $ABC$, $a$, $b$, $c$ are the sides opposite to angles $A$, $B$, $C$ respectively, and it is given that $a\cos C+(c-2b)\cos A=0$.
(I) Find $A$;
(II) If $a=2$, the area of $\triangle ABC$ is $\sqrt {3}$, find the value of $b+c$.

A: (I) $A=\dfrac {\pi}{3}$;

(II) $b+c=2\sqrt {3}$.

